HEADWORD: Mucky
<hw>Muck"y</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧k"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Filthy with muck; miry; <as>as, a <ex>mucky</ex> road</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Mucky</xex> filth.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vile, in a moral sense; sordid.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Mucky</qex> money and false felicity.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucocele</ent>⟦br⟧
